title: Appointments to Council on Human Reproductive Technology announced
content_text:
p> The Government today (April 10) announced the re-appointment of the Chairperson and six incumbent members, and the appointment of five new members to the Council on Human Reproductive Technology with effect from April 11, 2015. Re-appointments
---------------

Ms Adelaide Yu Hoi-man The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, welcomed the new members to the Council. He also expressed gratitude to the outgoing members, Dr Philemon Choi Yuen-wan, Ms Julian Ho Ying-fong, Ms Emily Kwong Yan-po, Dr Kathleen So Pik-han and Dr Tai Chark-man for their invaluable contributions

Kathleen So Pik-han and Dr Tai Chark-man for their invaluable contributions 
	to the Council during their term of office. Established in 2001 under the Human Reproductive Technology Ordinance, the 
	Council is tasked to regulate the conduct of reproductive technology 
	including embryo research in Hong Kong through a licensing system and the 
	publication of a Code of Practice for the relevant professions. Under section 4(2) of the Ordinance, the Council consists of 26 members from 
	a wide range of disciplines, including medical specialists, legal

a wide range of disciplines, including medical specialists, legal professionals, social worker, scholar in philosophy and ethics, psychologist, sociologist, local community leaders and government representatives.
